From: Florian Zaruba <florian.zaruba@axelera.ai>
Subject: [PATCH] Statically link libatomic in partial-static builds

libatomic.so.1 is not part of the manylinux baseline libraries, so
the Verilator binary fails to load on systems that don't have it in
the standard library path (e.g., CentOS 8 where libatomic lives in
/usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-redhat-linux/8/).

Add -static-libatomic alongside -static-libgcc and -static-libstdc++
in the partial static linking section to eliminate this runtime dependency.

diff --git a/configure.ac b/configure.ac
index abcdef1..1234567 100644
--- a/configure.ac
+++ b/configure.ac
@@ -565,6 +565,7 @@ AC_MSG_RESULT($CFG_ENABLE_PARTIAL_STATIC)
 if test "$CFG_ENABLE_PARTIAL_STATIC" = "yes"; then
   _MY_LDLIBS_CHECK_OPT(CFG_LDFLAGS_SRC, -static-libgcc)
   _MY_LDLIBS_CHECK_OPT(CFG_LDFLAGS_SRC, -static-libstdc++)
+  _MY_LDLIBS_CHECK_OPT(CFG_LDFLAGS_SRC, -static-libatomic)
   _MY_LDLIBS_CHECK_OPT(CFG_LDFLAGS_SRC, -Xlinker -gc-sections)
   LTCMALLOC="-Wl,--whole-archive -l:libtcmalloc_minimal.a -Wl,--no-whole-archive"
 else
